OL,3,C'Political movement' formed in
OL,4,CGuernsey ahead of 2025 election
OL,6,FAt the last States election in 2020,
OL,7,FDeputy St Pier formed the 'Guernsey
OL,8,FPartnership of Independents' which
OL,9,Fserved as a coalition of like-minded
OL,10,Findividuals rather than centred on
OL,11,Fpolicy.
OL,13,FIt won 10 out of the 38 seats at the
OL,14,Felection and was later re-named Future
OL,15,FGuernsey but dissolved months later.
OL,17,FDeputy Mark Helyar formed its rival,
OL,18,FThe Guernsey Party, which stood on a
OL,19,Fplatform resisting tax increases.
